It is alleged that a VW Golf 7 without registration stopped at the arrivals and departure&#8217;s terminal on Jones Street. JOHANNESBURG One person has been shot dead at the OR Tambo International Airport in an apparent assassination.It is alleged that VW Golf 7 without registration stopped at the arrivals and departure s terminal on Jones Street, and subsequently, an unconfirmed number of men stepped out and opened fire.An unconfirmed number of men climbed out of the car and opened fire.A man saw what happened. Like you see in the movies the black vehicle, before it stopped, three of the doors were open and people jumped out and started shooting. When I went past there, there was a body lying on the road. It looked like it had been shot to pieces. Emergency services and police are on the scene.It is unclear if any more people have been wounded at this stage.